\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $\Question$
\end_inset

Let
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
A=\begin{pmatrix}0.8 & 0.4\\
0.2 & 0.6
\end{pmatrix}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Compute the transition matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $P^{-1}AP$
\end_inset

 is diagonal.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\Answer$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note 
\begin_inset Formula $\det(\lambda I-A)=\lambda^{2}-1.4\lambda+0.4$
\end_inset

, so 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\in\left\{ 1,0.4\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 Thus, 
\begin_inset Formula $P=\begin{pmatrix}\v v_{1} & \v v_{0.4}\end{pmatrix}=\boxed{\begin{pmatrix}2 & 1\\
1 & -1
\end{pmatrix}}.$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

