\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $\Question$
\end_inset

Prove Theorem 4.3.12.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
Thm 4.3.12.
 (Semisimple Spectral Mapping).

\series default
 
\emph on
If 
\begin_inset Formula $(\lambda_{i})_{i=1}^{n}$
\end_inset

 are the eigenvalues of a semisimple matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in M_{n}(\F)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x)=a_{0}+a_{1}x+\cdots+a_{n}x^{n}$
\end_inset

 is a polynomial, then 
\begin_inset Formula $(f(\lambda_{i}))_{i=1}^{n}$
\end_inset

 are the eigenvalues of 
\begin_inset Formula $f(A)=a_{0}I+a_{1}A+\cdots+a_{n}A^{n}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\Answer$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
f(A) & = & a_{0}I+a_{1}A+\cdots+a_{n}A^{n}\\
 & = & a_{0}PP^{-1}+a_{1}P\Lambda P^{-1}+\cdots+a_{n}P\Lambda^{n}P^{-1}\\
 & = & Pf(\Lambda)P^{-1},
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\Lambda)$
\end_inset

 is composed of diagonal entries, so we have 
\begin_inset Formula $(f(\lambda_{i}))_{i=1}^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 The eigenvalues are 
\begin_inset Formula $(f(\lambda_{i}))_{i=1}^{n}$
\end_inset

 due to similarity.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\qed$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*

\family sans
