\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $\Question$
\end_inset

Prove: If 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 is an eigenvalue of the 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in M_{n}(\F)$
\end_inset

, then there exists a nonzero row vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\v x\T$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\v x\T A=\lambda\v x\T$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\Answer$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\det(\lambda I-A)=\det(\lambda I-A\T)$
\end_inset

, so e-vals of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 are also e-vals of 
\begin_inset Formula $A\T$
\end_inset

.
 So 
\begin_inset Formula $\exists\v v\in\F^{n}$
\end_inset

 s.t.
 
\begin_inset Formula $A\T\v v=\lambda\v v$
\end_inset

, so it follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $\v v\T A=\lambda\v v\T.$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\qed$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

