\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $\Question$
\end_inset

Prove Lemma 4.4.2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
Lemma 4.4.2.
 
\series default
\emph on
If 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is Hermitian and orthonormally similar to 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 is also Hermitian.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\Answer$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the given we know that 
\begin_inset Formula $B=PAP^{-1}$
\end_inset

 for some orthonormal 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 Hermitian so 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
B\H & = & \left(PAP^{-1}\right)\H\\
 & = & \left(PAP\H\right)\H\\
 & = & \left(P\H\right)A\H P\H\\
 & = & PAP\H\\
 & = & B.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\qed$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

