\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $\Question$
\end_inset

Given 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in M_{n}(\C)$
\end_inset

, define the 
\emph on
Rayleigh quotient 
\emph default
as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\rho(\v x)=\frac{\inn{\v x}{A\v x}}{\n{\v x}{}^{2}},
\]

\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\inn{\cdot}{\cdot}$
\end_inset

 is the usual inner product on 
\begin_inset Formula $\F{}^{n}$
\end_inset

.
 Show that the Rayleigh quotient can only take on real values for Hermitian
 matrices and only imaginary values for skew-Hermitian matrices.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\Answer$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\norm{\v x}^{2}\in\R$
\end_inset

, so it suffices to show that 
\begin_inset Formula $\inn{\v x}{A\v x}=\v x\H A\v x$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\overline{\v x\H A\v x} & = & \left(\v x\H A\v x\right)\H\\
 & = & \v x\H A\H\v x\\
 & = & \begin{cases}
\v x\H A\v x & (\inn{\v x}{A\v x}\in\R)\\
-\v x\H A\v x & (\mbox{\inn{\v x}{\mathit{A}\v x}\in\C\sm\R).}
\end{cases}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\qed$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*

\family sans
\color blue
Exercise 4.25.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Shaded
position "t"
